      <p>Think about the De'Markus Page case from our safety stories — the two-year-old who died after a 10x potassium phosphate overdose caused by a misplaced decimal point, with multiple safety barriers that failed to catch the error. If that organization had a fully implemented CANDOR process, how would the response have differed? What would the initial disclosure conversation look like for that family? What would Care for the Caregiver look like for the resident who made the error? Hold these questions as you work through this week's material on RCA2 and event management.</p>
